The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Saturday, March 13, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Saturday, March 13, 2004				 																What to do this weekend				 																																	Be there at The Telegraph-Calcutta Club national debate, presented on the club premises, 6.30 pm on Sunday. The motion: In the opinion of the house, the state should not fund the arts. The speakers: Rahul Bose, Mahesh Bhatt, Nafisa Ali, Jayant Kripalani, Rajeshwari Sachdev, Irfan Khan, Victor Banerjee and Shyamanand Jalan. Moderator: Dileep Padgaonkar.				 																Musical evenings				 																																	Attend a sarod recital by Ustad Amjad Ali Khan, presented by Hutch, in association with The Telegraph and Calcutta Club, at the club, 7 pm. Ustad Sabir Khan and Pandit Aninda Chattopadhyay on the tabla.				 																																	Check out a music-and-poetry session, featuring Jayashree Dasgupta and Prabhat Bose, at CIMA Gallery, at 6 pm. 				 																Disinvestment debate 				 																																	Cheer your favourites at the Xaverians vs Industry debate on Disinvestment in India, at St Xaviers College, 5 pm.
